==English==
===Noun===
'''heretike'''
# Archaic spelling of [[heretic]]
#*'''1604''' Reverend Cawdrey ''Table Aleph'': held that a 'Nicholaitan is an '''heretike''', like Nicholas, who held that wiues should bee commmon to all alike.'
#*  '''1556''' ''John Foxes Book of Martyrs'':The examination of Iohn Iackeson, had before Doct. Cooke, the xi. day of March. Anno.1556. FIrst when I came before him, he rayled on me, and called me '''heretike'''. I aunswered and saide: I am no '''heretike'''.
#* Date unknown: from ''The lawfulness of the Oath of Allegiance'' by Theophilis Higgins: "I speake out of perfect knowledge, because presently after this Popes death I my selfe was in Rome: and as Honorius Pope, was by three generall Councels accounted a Monothelite '''Heretike''' for his hereticall and doctrinall Epistles, which he wrote to Sergius Patriarke, and by him to the East Churches with divers other Popes, whose erroneous doctrinall Epistles cannot bee denied, nor by any meanes excused from errour or heresie, unlesse by some such a Golias, who will adventure after the censure of three Generall councels, and divers Popes to defend Honorius from being an '''Heretike'''," Ref The Christian History Institute.